{"type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"Analytics Dashboard Creator. Getting Started
===

Welcome to the Analytics Dashboard Creator for CloudBees Jenkins Analytics!

This screen allows you to create custom reports which you can share with other users using an embedded "Custom Analytics" view in CloudBees Jenkins Operations Center. 

In order to return back to Jenkins Web Interface, click on the _Jenkins_ tab on the top menu bar.

Additional Info
----

You can find more information in the [CloudBees Jenkins Analytics section](http://documentation.cloudbees.com/docs/cjoc-user-guide/analytics.html) of the CloudBees Jenkins Operations Center documentation.

CloudBees Jenkins analytics dashboards use [Kibana4](https://www.elastic.co/products/kibana) dashboards. The most of training materials are applicable to Analytics Dashboard Creator as well. Good third-party guidelines can be also found [here](https://www.timroes.de/2015/02/07/kibana-4-tutorial-part-1-introduction/) and [here](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-kibana-dashboards-and-visualizations)).

Creating dashboards
----

To get started, you can open an existing dashboard using the folder icon in the upper right hand corner, and then save it under a new name using the disk icon. It allows you to immediately get the new dashboard.

If you want to create a new dashboard, you need to perform the following steps:

1. Ensure that Kibana4 accepts indexes of {CJA} metrics. Go to _Settings_ tab in the top menu and check the _Index name or pattern_ field.
2. Ensure that your Elasticsearch instance contains enough test data for the dashboard evaluation.
3. Develop Kibana4 **visualizations** using the _Visualize_ tab in the top menu.
4. Aggregate **visualizations** into **dashboards** using the _Dashboard_ tab in the top menu.

After these steps you will be able to evaluate custom dashboards in Analytics Dashboard Creator web interface and update them on-demand.

Once you are happy with your custom dashboard, you can add an embedded Custom Jenkins Analytics view to CloudBees Jenkins Operations Center. To add the view, click the plus (```+```) button next to the built-in Build Analytics and Performance Analytics views on CloudBees Jenkins Operations Center.

Please note that any custom dashboard you create may not be supported in future versions of CloudBees Jenkins Operations Center. Also, please note that any change you make to the built-in dashboards, visualisations and other items (those starting with ```cjoc-```) will be reverted the next time Jenkins restarts or reconnects to the Elasticsearch instance. Your own data will be preserved."},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}
